BBC’s Thompson Says 1,000 More Jobs Could Move North, Times Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-10T18:34:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/bbc-s-thompson-says-1-000-more-jobs-could-move-north-times-says.html
The British Broadcasting Corp.’s
Director General Mark Thompson said a further 500 to 1,000 jobs
at the  BBC  could be moved to the corporation’s new offices in
Salford, the Times reported.  The first of about 2,300 BBC staff have already begun
moving into the new offices in the north of  England , the Times
said, citing remarks by Thompson.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  